parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch turns off unexpectedly
the key becomes stuck in the ignition
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the dashboard lights and gauges fail
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Key Fob and WIN Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the key fob and WIN module can cause the vehicle to not start, stall, or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The key fob becomes stuck in the ignition
the vehicle fails to start
the key fob is unable to eject from the ignition
the dashboard lights and gauges fail
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard lights and gauges fail
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag system malfunctions
and the airbag may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or shift into neutral while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly shifts into neutral
the transmission disengages while driving
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls
the check engine light comes on
and code P2767 is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case actuator can cause the vehicle to shift into neutral or fail to engage 4-wheel drive, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral
the transfer case fails to engage
the "Service 4WD System" warning light comes on
and the vehicle cannot be towed or used in 4-wheel drive mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch and Transmission Hydraulic System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
the vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is applied
and the vehicle collides with objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle rolling away can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backward without warning
the vehicle rolls away when placed into drive
and the vehicle fails to engage parking gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Random Engine Shutdown and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shutdown of the engine while driving can cause loss of power steering, brakes, and propulsion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine shuts down without warning
the vehicle slows down
the radio and other accessories turn off
the steering becomes loose and unpredictable
the power brakes and propulsion are lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The power steering fluid leaks
the power steering pump fails
the power steering line develops holes
the steering becomes loose and unpredictable
the vehicle loses power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion unit can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The rack and pinion unit fails
the steering becomes loose and unpredictable
the vehicle loses control
the unit needs to be replaced frequently.
